==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|ko|-}} {{ko-l|^훈민정음|訓民正音}}, literally "correct sounds to educate the people".

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|head=Hunmin Jeongeum}}

# {{lb|en|archaic}} The [[phonetic]] [[script]] in which [[Korean]] is written, now usually called [[Hangeul]]. 
